title: For Sale/Trade:  SKS Sporter w/ AK mags
postcontent:
Hi everybody I'm looking to trade my SKS sporter.  This is the carbine that takes AK mags.  I bought it last fall from another member and haven't really used it.  It comes with 5 magazines and about 180 rounds.  This is a picture I found, it looks just like mine.  

One thing I've noticed about this rifle, every once in a while when you cycle the action as the bolt closes it drops the hammer as well.  Obviously this can cause a slamfire.  I shot it once and put one magazine through without any slamfires and then I cycled one more magazine by hand and got one slamfire.  My thinking is that someone messed with the trigger group.  It might need a new sear or disconnector or something.  I'm not a gunsmith so I don't want to mess with it, but I believe all the parts for the trigger group are relatively inexpensive and available.

title: For Sale:  Hakim Battle Rifle  8mm Semi Adjustable gas system
postcontent: If youre looking, you know what these are. Gas operated, Egyptian built on Swedish machinery with Sweish steel. These are based on Ljungman Swedish rifles that Egypt had converted to a larger size to accept the 8mm ammo they had tons of in the 1950s. It has 10 round mags but lots of 25 and 30 rounders are out there. Spare parts are available as well. A truly unique design that cocks FORWARD. It will be the center of attention at the range. Has the recoil of an AK or less due to its size and weight and especially the muzzle brake designed into it. The blast moves the partitions at the indoor range outward every shot. 8mm ammo is still around for under 40 cents a round. In better shape than many and there are only a few thousand around. Metal surfaces are 85% plus and the wood, while dinged up. is better than most as the storage from the 1960s wasnt kind to the wood and I dont know how they trained, but they beat on the stocks. Keep in mind that I am using terms as compared to regular firearms and not military ones which dont come with deep bluing and smooth finishes to start, so this is nice like a nice Mauser. Pictures are good and I can send closeups but it looks better in person as the flash reflects weird on the metal surface. Bore has very good rifling though lost the shine from decades of corrosive ammo BUT the gas system and adjustable valve is pristine. I took it apart totally and cleaned every crevice. The adjustable gas system allows use of HOT Turkish ammo, or 8mm from different continents and decades that are very different. Short of a BAR in 30-06 or Dragunov 7.62x54, 8mm is the only other full size caliber and the only other 8mm semis are very expensive, as in double or triple the price. Local sales with ID or will ship to FFL for $32 (heavy gun)

location: Concord, East Bay, San Francisco, California
postcontent:
Bad news, CA state Senate passed two bills to ban this rifle.  Get it before prices go back to $2000.   Why wait for round 2 of the buying panic. 

This is a new custom Palmetto build AR15 chambered in 5.56 Nato with bullet button installed and one ten round magazine by C products!

If you're looking for an AR15, this is an awesome choice for your first black rifle.  Most AR15s that have 16in barrels run a carbine length gas system with a semi-auto bolt carrier group.  The mid length gas system actually runs smoother than the carbine, producing less recoil.  This allows you to stay on target better than your friend with a carbine AR15.  On top of that, you'll have the full auto bolt carrier group which will allow your rifle to cycle more smoothly because it's a little heavier than the semi-auto.  

Palmetto makes great rifles!  The chrome lined 1-7 twist barrel is made by FN manufacturing, a well known producer of excellent barrels.  The bolt carrier group is the Palmetto M-16 MPI, pretty much as good as it gets, built to last.  The 6-position buttstock is made by Blackhawk and I threw a Magpul MOE grip on there.  The lower parts are from Palmetto as well.  Fortunately, this one came with a pretty good trigger.  Sometimes you get lucky!

Preferred transfer location is City Arms East in Pleasant Hill.
